    <Note Caller="1" LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="" LastEditedBy="">
      <References/>
      <Content>ὄλεθρος[a] suggests a type of ruin or destruction which is somewhat more violent and extensive than in the case of φθορά[a] ({D:20.38}).</Content>
    </Note>
    <Note Caller="2" LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="" LastEditedBy="">
      <References/>
      <Content>The meaning of ὀλοθρεύω and ὄλεθρος[b] in {D:20.34} is considerably stronger and more intense than the meanings in {D:20.31}.</Content>
    </Note>
